cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for weakly supervised segmentation of medical images using extreme point clicks. This involves using a fully convolutional network to segment the organ of interest based on the provided user clicks. The paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image segmentation. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it involves training a model using weak supervision. Additionally, it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category as it deals with medical images, and the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it involves training a neural network.
